==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin [[materia]] (matter, stuff, material), derivative of Latin [[mater]] (mother).
===Noun===
'''Matter'''
#The basic structural component of the [[universe]].  Matter always consists of a [[mass]] and a [[volume]].
#A kind of substance.
#:''vegetable matter''
#A reason for concern; being amiss
#:''What's the matter?''
#A situation.
#:''a trivial matter''
#A cause.
#:''a matter for concern''
